               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> Long paper roll, containing officer copies, <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1475">saec. xv exeunt.</origDate>, of:
                  (1) grant to the earls of Salesbury of 1000 marks annually from the exchequer; imperfect.
                  (2) Inspeximus of grant by <persName>
                           <forename>Alesia</forename>, widow of <persName>
                              <forename>Thomas</forename> E. of Lancaster</persName>
                        </persName> 
                  to <persName>Edw. II</persName> of various manors, etc. <origDate when="1322-07-09">9 July 16 Edw. II (1322)</origDate>.
                        (3) Inquisition post mortem of  <persName><forename>Thomas</forename>, earl of Salisbury</persName>, <origDate notAfter="1429" notBefore="1428">7 Hen. VI (1428-9)</origDate>.
                  (4) Inquisition for <persName>sir <forename>Rich</forename>. de <surname>Montacute</surname>, knt.</persName> from the Escheat Roll for Somerset, <origDate notBefore="1429" notAfter="1430">8 Hen. VI (1429-30)</origDate>.</p>
